The standard approaches to generate age, gender, and organ-specific risk estimates are based on the so-called excess absolute risk, ear. It denotes the additional risk of a person of gender S, after an exposure to organ dose D
T at the age e, to be clinically diseased with a specific radiation-induced cancer at the age a or, more specifically, in the interval [a, a + 1). It is commonly calculated from
