T and attained age a is as high as his normal cancer risk. Estimates of the excess (relative) risk for specific organs are usually derived from cancer incidence data of the LSS, where a linear dose dependence is commonly assumed for solid tumors, while a linear-quadratic approach provides better results for leukemia. The most recent models are summarized in the BEIR-VII report [1].

The site-specific excess absolute lifetime risk or lifetime attributable risk, LAR
